text: Donnchad mac Maíl Coluim (Modern Gaelic: Donnchadh mac Mhaoil Chaluim)Donnchad mac Maíl Coluim is the Mediaeval Gaelic form renamed as Duncan II (before c. 1060 – 12 November 1094) was king of Scots. He was son of Malcolm III (Máel Coluim mac Donnchada) and his first wife Ingibiorg Finnsdottir, widow of Thorfinn Sigurdsson. ==References== Category:Kings and Queens of Scotland Category:1050s births Category:1094 deaths Category:11th century in Scotland
title: Duncan II of Scotland
